main event: A bright green object with a neon glow, the size of a full moon, descended rapidly and then disappeared.
interesting points: The object was described as a bright green object with a neon glow, the size of a full moon.
The object descended rapidly before disappearing.
The witness had seen similar objects on two prior occasions, one in Africa in 1952 and one approximately 225 miles north of Colorado Springs in 1956.
The witness had read and discussed UFOs extensively.
The report concluded the object was likely a meteor.
sighted object: Bright green object with a neon glow, the size of a full moon
location: 26-30 miles north of Rock Springs, Wyoming
